Thanks to the gorgeous mural that capes the entire front exterior of Fathers, this spot caught my eye before even stepping inside. Then upon entering and seeing the rustic brick walls, hip decor, and cool art fixtures, I was instantly in love. I immediately thought "wow, this is the place I'd be a weekly (maybe daily) regular at if I lived here."  Fathers serves up a delicious looking brunch menu from 9:00am-4:30pm and then transitions into an equally delicious looking dinner menu from 5:00pm-12:00am. As I had just eaten breakfast, I didn't get any food, but I did peek at the menu and everything looked delish! On top of that they also have a mean cocktail list. If cocktails aren't your thing, they do have a cafe that serves up non-alcoholic beverages, coffees, and teas.  Our server was so kind and friendly and even though we were there to work on our laptops and not to get food, she still diligently checked in on us.  I'm not in New York often, but if I'm ever back, I'd especially love to pop in here again during one of the nights they have live music going on.  If you're in this part of Brooklyn, would highly recommend visiting Fathers and staying for a while.

My partner and I stopped in for brunch today and it was a total let down from the moment we stepped in until we left. I've lived here in the neighborhood for over 4 1/2 years now and have frequented this establishment several times over that span of time. Today was the WORST! We sat ourselves at an open table. I went up to the bar to place my order along with several other patrons who were also waiting. It took about 10 min. for someone to take my order. During that time I witnessed one girl who seemed to be the manager/shift leader be rude to the other 2 male employees. I overheard one guy say to her "don't be mean to me." Her attitude was very off-putting. When I finally was approached, I was told "just a minute". Another person came to take my order but I was then overlooked. I let it go. I finally placed our order which was:  Lumberdad Breakfast Mushroom Hash sans avocado ( my usual go to) 1 Side of bacon 1 Americano  My coffee came and we proceeded to wait. After trying my coffee, my partner wanted one as well. I went back up to the bar to order another Americano, 1 side of half & half and I added a side of poached eggs to my Mushroom Hash because I forgot to add this initially (probably because it took so long for my order to be taken in the 1st place). It took yet another 10 minutes to place that order. Because of the long wait, my coffee was lukewarm by the time I got back to our table. At this point, I was highly annoyed by how our experience was going. Our food arrived and we were missing the bacon & poached eggs. I get why the poached eggs would come after receiving our food but the bacon wasn't even on our tab. I forgot to mention to my partner that they couldn't substitute the chorizo for bacon and that I'd just ordered her a side of bacon. When I mentioned to the server that I ordered a side she was also confused bc she thought someone substituted the chorizo for bacon. She said "We don't do substitutions for the chorizo. And if anyone told you that, they should be fired." I made it a point to mention that there wasn't a substitution and the person who took our first order did mention this and that I ordered a SIDE of bacon. Her comment totally threw me off and left a bad taste in my mouth; combined with how I witnessed her treat the employees prior to this. This was the same girl who had been rude to the other employees. She put our order in with the kitchen and came back to say it would be out in 2 min. I was now completely unhappy with EVERYTHING & her attitude towards the other employees. My mushroom hash is supposed to come with CRISPY potatoes (Johnny cakes) & it was soggy. I've had this dish several times before and It has never come out like this. The Johnny cake & Mushrooms were under what seemed like a pre-washed BOX of arugula. NOTE TO KITCHEN: Put the arugula/beet salad on the side so the potatoes and mushrooms stay crispy. This was a fail!!!  The bacon & eggs didn't come out for another 10 min and by this time my partner had finished her lumberdad breakfast without having the bacon.  When the bacon & eggs came I just wanted to wrap it all up in a box & leave. I couldn't stand being there for another minute. I debated not tipping at all but I did. When I went to get the check there was one girl at the bar washing/cleaning up. This section of the bar was empty. Two other patrons approached the bar after I had been standing there for a couple of minutes and she proceeded to help them. I'm SURE she saw me approach first. This also left me feeling overlooked AGAIN!  I'm not sure if it was because it's a holiday and they were extremely busy but the customer service today sucked! The staff needs to be more attentive and maybe have designated roles as they all seemed to be trying to do everything and maybe their wires were getting crossed. I don't think I'll ever return and If I do, it'll be on a day where NONE of the staff that was there today is on shift or when it's not so busy. Also, to the staff; acknowledging customers settles the inconvenience of having to wait so long. DO BETTER!

Just left this place 5 mins ago. I can't speak to the brunch here as we were not seated. I wanted to like this place but not matter how good the food may be customer service is paramount.  My girlfriend and I enter and wait to be seated. We were promptly asked if we were a party of two. So far so good. The interaction starts to go downhill from here though.  We let the person know that we're a party of two and she said I'll need to setup a table. No problem yet. We clarify that we'd like an outside table as people inside were clearing out. The response was a sharp "as I said I need to clean up a table I'll be right with you". Strike one.  I think I'm pretty reasonable and can understand this clarification may have felt uncessary if I put myself in their shoes but snapping at your customer isn't the start of a positive dining experience.  The next thing that happens is she starts to wipe down several INDOOR tables. So either completing this other task was more important than the customer in front of you, there was a misunderstanding of the request or she acted in spite. I'd like to think it's the middle option. Strike two.  So a gentleman asked whether we were being helped. Great now we're getting back on track. As the first person continues to tender to the indoor tables we let him know we're waiting for an outside table and he say she may not understand that and walks over to speak with her. Awesome! He comes backs and says we should be good to go soon.  Two women enter after us while we are waiting and speak to the gentleman we just spoke with. They ask about seating and specifically can they sit outside. They were told the don't need to wait and just sit in the back. Strike three.  This is the exact request we spoke with two different people at this point while we wait for the original person to finish preparing indoor tables. At this point we exit immediately. Why wouldn't two people give us this option and make us wait while another patron was provided this option immediately.  I really wanted to like Father Knows Best but I can't recommend this place. The details matter and being thoughtful and considerate goes a long way.

Really nice neighborhood bar. Lots of space, with a nice courtyard in the back. Great to grab a coffee and work on your laptop, or to party it up.
Great food and cafe drinks, fantastic vibe, nice views, super close to Wilson stop on the L, and REAL OG BUSHWICK PEOPLE serving that get 'er done and don't mind all the hipsters
Muushhrooom hash
BEST Chicken club sandwich I've ever had.  Laid back ambiance, good music, friendly accommodating staff...outdoor patio you can smoke cigs on...free wifi...what else could I ask for
Best place for breakfast OR drinks. Wonderfully kind and warm people, nothing but mellow vibes and good coffees.
Dank pancakes and Johnny Pancakes are delicious!!
Love this place great food and drinks
Every time I come I always get their Macho Manachos Brunch and freshly squeezed lemonade... IT'S AMAZING!!
Great cocktails and food, with great service and clean bathrooms ! Love this local spot
When visiting Brooklyn this is our favorite spot for food and spirits.

Honestly I love this bar. Great food, solid liquor selection. Only reason I give it 3 stars is that it's very clear some of the bar staff have never bartended anywhere else. The bar is half full and I waited 5 minutes to be greeted and I'm waiting another 5 for a drink. Not terribly bad service but very slow.
Get vibe and cheap drinks

*I came during post-work hours before it got too busy.* Cute little place. Bartenders were attentive and personable, prices weren't terrible. There is patio space for nice days, bar and table seating inside. There isn't much of a happy hour. I didn't try the food. A live band was setting up on the back patio as I sat. I would definitely come back!
Kinda expensive!
Fun place and great food
Kinda pricey, but DJ was great! Food selection is decent.
Food is outstanding! Service left a little to be desired.
Good vibes, good music

Great neighborhood bar with good prices and cool bar tenders. There’s a back patio and front porch area for chilling outside. They serve food that is really good as well. Some nights feature DJ’s and others a live jazz band. Always a welcoming and relaxed vibe.

I was with a friend in the area and there didn't seem to be many food options in that particular neighborhood. A stranger on the street recommended this place. It was a 10 minute walk, but I really liked the atmosphere and food. Between us; we got a kale salad, hot pretzel bread and split a ham & cheese sandwich. Everything tasted good. Neither of us drank alcohol that night. But, they seemed to have some cool drink options. A band was setting up to play as we were leaving. It was around 10 pm on a Tuesday night. If I find myself in that area, I will definitely check this place out again.
Great cocktails and cool ambiance.  Wait stuff was very friendly and they have a great outdoor space.
Simple friendly bar and grill. Good food and drinks.
Great place! Check out the jazzy jam sessions on Mondays evening :)
Service was great, and so were the drinks. Did not order any food so cannot comment on that. A decent place overall.
I’m going to be honest and say this place is uptight and full of trust fund kids. I thought it would be a great place to chill and study, but the food was hot or miss a lot of the time.
Chill atmosphere, but get here early on the weekends!
One of my favorite places in the area.. great for brunch, drinks or just to spend a nice time!
What a cute homey little bar restaurant. The cocktails are great. Menu is limited but good stuff. I like the Mac and cheese. The backyard and soft music was great.

(Translated by Google) Great place, very welcoming, we loved it. In addition it is very good. Have a good tasting.  (Original) Super endroit, très accueillant, on a adoré. En plus c'est très bon. Have a good tasting.
LOVE THIS SPOT!
The couple of bartenders that were working on jazz night were quick, friendly, and personable. The prices on beer are very good, and the music was solid all night.

A very cool and low key place to hang out with friends after work and have a drink and some snacks. Nice atmosphere. The prices are average, and they never seem to have happy hour specials when I've been, but not unreasonable. I love getting their cheddar scallion biscuits with chipotle honey butter. It's definitely enough to split with another person, or just eat yourself, if you're feeling extra hungry!
The best breakfast in Brooklyn 😊

Went in for their brunch on an early Wednesday afternoon. Not a lot of people. Many tables to choose from. We sat by the bar and our orders were taken immediately. The coffee was a bit expensive for the quantity but the expresso packs a punch. Interesting vegetarian options. Had the mushroom hash sandwich and added the pouched eggs, excellent combo. The mom bod sandwich is a good startup. Many vegan options to choose from. Free wifi. Will be coming back.
Land mark of bushwick
Great music. A spot to get to know the locals.
This bar is super cute and trendy. When we went on a Friday it was busy and the DJ was good.
Brunch was sooooooo good
I honestly had low expectations. But I had the lumberdad breakfast and it was amazing. I definitely recommend this place to anyone. Coffee was on point as well

Righteous local spot. Love the staff! Frequent several times a week different times of the day. Always consistent. Mushroom Hash and Egg sandwich for brunch is go to. Homemade Soft Pretzel, mom bod, and macho nachos to go for dinner. Sometimes do specials which are always worth ordering and pop ups. A+
The food is pretty great across the board. Summer they have watermelon margs - they serve a group one for $40 in a bottom half of a watermelon. Friendly / laidback servers / bartenders
Hipest, most delicious spot to relax.

The place has decent food, and a decent drink selection.  The BIGGEST issue is the acoustics, which are awful. This space is extremely small, but they host live bands and bad DJ's at almost all hours of the day, which are painfully loud, to the point where you can't hear yourself think. Even worse are the young, drunk, rich NYU grads who host open mic nights on the weekends to tell "stories from the neighborhood", by which they mean the stories from every white 20-something who has moved here two years ago...  It really only exists because there are so few other options in the area, and it is very conveniently located next to the L.
Love love love Father's! I have been a few times at night, but I mostly go in the morning for coffee. The staff is super friendly and they don't mind you sitting down for a while to be productive!
Lunchtime visit and have to say Iwas extremely impressed!!! Nice music and the Mucho macho something or the other was off the charts!!
Great vibes, music, drinks and good !
Very nice place lovely for couples
Favorite resturaunt in Bushwick hands down!
Tried the sandwiches and they're pretty good.
Can be a hit or a miss. Some nights they have the music so damned loud you can't hear yourself think, let alone talk. Not good for a bar space! Hinders mingling! Nice smoking area in the back!
Nice

This place.... their bartenders are a piece of work. I go in and politely ask how we go about ordering (you order food from the bar and I didn't know that). This bartender would not even look at me. (Rude) Then he shoved the menu at me and said yes you obviously order here. I said you're not too friendly. He looked at someone else and laughed. So it's THAT kind of bar..... great food though.
Calm atmoshphere. Fun menu.
Homey deliciousness. Have to check out the yard.
Amazing food, banana bread pancakes are incredible.
Great live music, fun comfort food and cocktails. Mostly I just love the vibe. It's become a regular hang out for me.

There is a sign on the wall that tells you when the next L train is coming, in real time!!  Next time you are waiting for a wilson L train you need to go here for a drink. Usually nice and quiet with events happening later on in the evening. Interesting bites and a good range of drinks.

Overpriced, my drink was really not worth 10 dollars (if they say coffee with whiskey and condensed milk... It is literally that. In a regular mug, barely stirred). And the servers seemed kind.of annoyed at making it.

Great place for drinks, food, and a good time! Greg is the best bartender, and the atmosphere never disappoints. Once a month they have an acoustic night that brings incredible local musicians together.
Perfect afterwork spot
Love this place, I have visited 3 times. Wednesdays is trivia night. I had the Sloppy Puppy Burger and Papa’s Draft. The WiFi speed is superb. And above all the staff is just the best.
Fantastic atmosphere, great outdoor patio, jazz nights, trivia nights, brunch, yoga, serve both coffee and alcohol as well as food... I'm headed there now!

I'm going to come here all the time. The menu is in Consolas! That's my favorite font!  (Either that or Lucida Console. You can tell by the g's. The Lucida Console g is much less wild.)  The food is great, unpresumptious and affordable, while still being hip as HECK, well prepared, they have Biscuits which is a sleeper hit for sure!  I liked the cocktail I bought. [passion fruit, tequila, chili sour salt on rim] They also have events most days of the week. Yeah!
Great food and great atmosphere. Our server was awesome. Killer art on the walls and out back. Definitely recommend jazz brunch.
The food has not impressed me, Mexican cuisine on the genres, the place on the other hand is very nice.

FKB is okay. I'm from Denver so maybe I've just had my fill of lightly-pretentious eateries. The staff was kind but the menu is a little pricy when the food is adequate - not poor quality but nothing special. Pretty normal "farm to table" type foods. I probably won't go back.
Solid little neighborhood bar. Large patio. The food is good. Wish the beer menu was more varied.
Unpretentious, fun, and a place to be seen!
Good place to drink, talk and relax.
Delicious food, great service, good vegan options.
nice quiet place for cheap drinks

Really cool homie spot to check out if you're in the area, super cozy and a great place to sit down and have a coffee or a cocktail. There's also live music if you come in at the right time, some really cool looking sounding bands. *Make sure you try the biscuit it's really good*

Went on a Sunday for brunch, had a great Bloody Mary and very friendly service. The woman was awesome and really friendly and the 2 guys (bartender and server) were cute and friendly and efficient. I really liked my food, the mushroom hash and would  definitely go back.
Amazing service, friendly staff and the food is on point. Highly recommend brunch here
Nice cafe during the day/bar at night. Chill music
Great brunch spot, great coffee, great service. Big back patio for the warmer temperatures which is always a big plus. Can't recommend brunch enough though.
Good atmosphere

A well designed, artistic, and inviting bar that features a myriad of beers, liquors, and cocktails combined with some very unique food choices that are quite succulent.  The crowd is friendly and light, live jazz music was incredible, and the bartenders were extraordinary friendly.  It is easy to see why it's so popular, and without I will return the next time I'm in Brooklyn.
Awesome rich breakfast. Nice staff. Can highly recommend.
the jalapeno mac and cheese is out of this world

A lovely spot for breakfast or brunch, but also a great bar scene at night. Live music a few nights a week, trivia, reasonably priced alcohol, and a relaxed atmosphere. I will definitely be back soon!
Excellent art, atmosphere, service, and patrons.
Great little place to grab a bite. Friendly staff great atmosphere and heslthy menu.
Oh my god.. the pretzels are amazing

Chill place. Nice backyard, adequate.

Cool and young place with great attitude. The food is nice and the drinks are really good. If it is a warm day, the back yard is highly recommended.
Always good food. Good drinks. Its am easy go to for any mood.
Excellent neighborhood pub. Lots of activities over the week days.
Great food great drinks great service great music

One of the two best spots to hangout off of the Wilson Avenue Station on the L Train. At night it's where the party is the most turned up. During the day it's a bit quieter. This is probably the busiest spot in the area. I think most people in the neighborhood like it.
